### Vouch API — REST Client collection
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP Client.
### Set @token after logging in (copy data.tokens.access_token from /auth/github).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1
@token = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
@companyToken = PASTE_COMPANY_TOKEN_HERE
@companyRefreshToken = PASTE_COMPANY_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
@projectId = PASTE_PROJECT_ID
@problemId = PASTE_PROBLEM_ID
@username = ada

### Health
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### --- Auth ---

### GitHub OAuth callback (exchange code → tokens)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/github
Content-Type: application/json

{ "code": "GITHUB_OAUTH_CODE" }

### Refresh tokens
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}" }

### Logout (revoke refresh token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}" }

### Get own profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Companies ---

### Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/companies/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Corp",
  "email": "hiring@acme.com",
  "password": "S3cur3P@ssw0rd!",
  "website": "https://acme.com",
  "size": "medium"
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/companies/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "hiring@acme.com", "password": "S3cur3P@ssw0rd!" }

### Refresh company tokens
POST {{baseUrl}}/companies/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refresh_token": "{{companyRefreshToken}}" }

### Company logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/companies/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{companyToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refresh_token": "{{companyRefreshToken}}" }

### Get company profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/companies/me
Authorization: Bearer {{companyToken}}

### --- Users ---

### Public builder profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{username}}

### Update my profile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Ada Lovelace", "bio": "Shipping QueryForge.", "website_url": "https://example.com" }

### Connect Stripe (read-only OAuth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/me/stripe
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "code": "STRIPE_OAUTH_CODE" }

### --- Projects ---

### Discover (paginated, filterable)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects?sort=mrr&page=1&limit=20

### Create a project
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "QueryForge",
  "tagline": "Visual SQL builder for analysts",
  "description": "Drag-and-drop SQL.",
  "live_url": "https://queryforge.dev",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/ada/queryforge",
  "payment_link": "https://buy.stripe.com/demo",
  "tags": ["saas", "developer-tools"],
  "for_sale": false
}

### Single project
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}

### Update a project
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tagline": "Now with AI query suggestions", "status": "live" }

### Archive a project
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Scores ---

### Leaderboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/scores?limit=25

### Builder score + breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/scores/{{username}}

### Trigger recalculation (async)
POST {{baseUrl}}/scores/recalculate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Problems (demand board) ---

### List problems
GET {{baseUrl}}/problems?sort=upvotes&status=open

### Post a problem
POST {{baseUrl}}/problems
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Self-hosted status page that ingests Prometheus",
  "description": "Clean status page wired to existing Prometheus alerts.",
  "tags": ["infra"],
  "budget_min": 500,
  "budget_max": 2000
}

### Single problem
GET {{baseUrl}}/problems/{{problemId}}

### Claim a problem (emails the poster)
POST {{baseUrl}}/problems/{{problemId}}/claim
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Upvote a problem
POST {{baseUrl}}/problems/{{problemId}}/upvote
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Reviews ---

### Post a review
POST {{baseUrl}}/reviews
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "project_id": "{{projectId}}", "rating": 5, "body": "Replaced a paid tool for us." }

### Reviews for a project
GET {{baseUrl}}/reviews/project/{{projectId}}

### --- Uploads ---

### Get a presigned R2 upload URL, then PUT the file to upload_url
POST {{baseUrl}}/uploads/presign
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "content_type": "image/png" }
